Suzy is a nice enough prof but honestly her accent made it difficult to understand her at times:/ 
When I or anyone else would ask questions she often brushed them off. that being said super interesting course content, loved the PRAAT stuff, but not the greatest at delivering the lectures or at communicating in a clear and respectful way.

I was nervous about this class but Dr. Ahn is a great professor and looks for ways to be understanding of her students. Goes over material thoroughly and multiple times. Lots of practice. 4 homework assignments (counts best 3) with straightforward criteria for the most part, a PRAAT segmentation that was not difficult, midterm, and a final
